        {
          "id": 147527,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Nernst equation</span></span></span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 147528,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Henderson-Hasselbalch equation</span></span></span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 147529,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Gibbs-Donnan effect</span></span></span></span></p>"
        },
        {
          "id": 147530,
          "text": "<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Hodgkin-Huxley equation</span></span></span></span></p>"
        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">A medical researcher is studying ion distribution across a membrane in a solution containing non-diffusible ions. To explain this phenomenon, they refer to a specific principle. Which of the following best describes the distribution of permeant ions between two compartments separated by a semipermeable membrane in the presence of non-diffusible ions in one of the compartments?</span></span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q8566592",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 33619,
      "difficulty_level": "beginner",
      "subjects_id": [
        2
      ],
      "solution": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Ans. C) Gibbs-Donnan effect</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Option C:&nbsp;</span></span></strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Correct. The Gibbs-Donnan effect describes the <strong>distribution</strong> of <strong>ions</strong> across a <strong>semipermeable membrane</strong> when <strong>non-diffusible ions</strong> are present in <strong>one</strong> of the compartments, leading to an <strong>unequal distribution</strong> of <strong>diffusible ions</strong> across the <strong>membrane</strong>.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Explanation:</span></span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><strong>Option A:</strong>&nbsp;</span></span><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><strong>Incorrect</strong>. The <strong>Nernst equation</strong> calculates the <strong>equilibrium potential</strong> for a particular <strong>ion</strong> across a membrane, but it doesn&#39;t address the distribution of diffusible ions affected by non-diffusible ions.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><strong>Option B:</strong>&nbsp;</span></span><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><strong>Incorrect</strong>. This equation is used to <strong>calculate</strong> the <strong>pH</strong> of a <strong>buffer solution</strong> and is not directly related to ion distribution across a membrane in the presence of non-diffusible ions.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Option D:&nbsp;</span></span></strong><strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Incorrect</span></span></strong><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">. The <strong>Hodgkin-Huxley equation</strong> is related to <strong>nerve action potentials</strong> and <strong>ion conductance</strong>, not specifically to the scenario described.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><u><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Educational Objective:</span></span></u></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-IN\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">The objective is to understand the <strong>Gibbs-Donnan effect</strong> and its significance in explaining the <strong>distribution</strong> of ions across a <strong>membrane</strong> in the <strong>presence</strong> of <strong>non-diffusible ions</strong>.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Refer: Guyton and Hall Textbook of Medical Physiology, 14<sup>th</sup> Edition, Pg no: 308</span></span></strong></span></span></p>",
